cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA 

The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on making as few assumptions as possible about the environment suggests a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the experiments and implementation of the algorithms suggest a potential connection to multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
